# IIS-DeployApp Logging

## Log File Location

The IIS-DeployApp scripts write to a dedicated log file on the target server:

```
C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\Opt\data\IIS-DeployApp\FkLog_YYYYMMDD.log
```

- **Date format:** `YYYYMMDD` using current date (e.g., `FkLog_20260217.log`)
- **UNC path:** `C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\Opt\data\IIS-DeployApp\`
- **Local path on server:** `E:\opt\data\IIS-DeployApp\`
- **Format:** Pipe-delimited: `timestamp|server|level|type|pid|script|function|line|user|message`

## Reading the Log

When asked to check the IIS-DeployApp log:

1. Compute the filename: `FkLog_{date}.log` (default: today)
2. Copy from UNC to local before searching (see general remote-log-reading rule)
3. Look for `IIS-RedeployAll`, `IIS-DeployApp`, `Deploy-IISSite`, `ERROR`, `FATAL`, `JOB_FAILED`, `JOB_STARTED`, `JOB_COMPLETED`
